Vintage illustration of an ancient tree with deep roots and branching limbs, where each major branch splits into smaller branches holding ornate wax seals and elaborate skeleton keys dangling from ribbons. The tree grows from an open leather-bound ledger, its roots wrapping around the spine. Warm sepia tones with touches of deep burgundy and gold leaf accents. Aged parchment texture throughout, with subtle coffee stains and foxing marks. The composition suggests hierarchy and trust flowing from root to branches, with morning light filtering through creating dappled shadows on the keys and seals below.
